1
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:15,708
[JEANNE]
Montmorency.

2
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:17,875
[MONTMORENCY]
Jeanne!

3
00:00:17,958 --> 00:00:19,083
Where are you?!

4
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:22,958
[JEANNE]
Montmorency. Save me.

5
00:00:23,041 --> 00:00:24,041
I'm coming!

6
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:25,500
[panting]

7
00:00:25,583 --> 00:00:26,791
Out of my way!

8
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,500
Get out of my way!

9
00:00:28,583 --> 00:00:29,791
Move!

10
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:31,625
[JEANNE]
Save me.

11
00:00:31,708 --> 00:00:34,208
No. No! You fools.

12
00:00:34,291 --> 00:00:38,083
I said, get the hell
out of my way!

13
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:44,291
[panting]

14
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:51,625
[ALENCON] You lost consciousness
on the battlefield.

15
00:00:51,708 --> 00:00:53,166
Quite the blunder.

16
00:00:53,250 --> 00:00:54,458
Where am I?

17
00:00:54,541 --> 00:00:56,791
[ALENCON]
Augustine's Fortress.

18
00:00:56,875 --> 00:00:58,500
We snatched it back
from the English

19
00:00:58,583 --> 00:01:00,708
amid the confusion
of the last battle.

20
00:01:00,791 --> 00:01:02,208
In a way, it's thanks to--

21
00:01:02,291 --> 00:01:03,708
Wait, Jeanne!

22
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:07,208
[groans] She died
in that battle, didn't she?

23
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:08,958
It appeared that way, but no.

24
00:01:09,041 --> 00:01:10,208
[gasps]

25
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:44,458
[ASTAROTH]
She has lost her heart.

26
00:02:44,541 --> 00:02:45,958
And that wound from
the Holy Lance

27
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:47,791
isn't healing as it should.

28
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:50,166
Fortunately, her head
is still fully intact.

29
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:54,666
The Philosopher's Stone is just
barely keeping her alive.

30
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:57,708
She's in a comatose state
to avoid dying completely.

31
00:02:57,791 --> 00:03:00,583
If she wasn't, I doubt
the stone could do much.

32
00:03:00,666 --> 00:03:03,041
[BATARD]
I understand what you're saying,

33
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:05,333
but it's still
very difficult to believe.

34
00:03:05,416 --> 00:03:06,875
If she has yet to perish,

35
00:03:06,958 --> 00:03:09,291
then there must be a way
we can save her.

36
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:11,083
Am I correct, Astaroth?

37
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:12,166
Indeed.

38
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:19,125
The legendary sword Excalibur.

39
00:03:19,208 --> 00:03:22,666
It's a Philosopher's Stone with
incredible healing abilities.

40
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:25,333
If we can attain that blade,
then there's a chance.

41
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:30,958
Wait. Montmorency,
you have to listen to me.

42
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,416
Even if the young maiden
is revived,

43
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,125
our troop size
can no longer hope

44
00:03:37,208 --> 00:03:40,375
to match the English army
after our latest retreat.

45
00:03:40,458 --> 00:03:42,166
We were fortunate
to take this fortress,

46
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:44,375
but we cannot
defend it forever.

47
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:46,500
We need troops, badly.

48
00:03:46,583 --> 00:03:48,875
Two thousand soldiers more,
at the bare minimum.

49
00:03:48,958 --> 00:03:50,875
What do you expect me
to do about it?

50
00:03:50,958 --> 00:03:52,708
The blade, Excalibur is hidden

51
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:54,625
somewhere in the forest
of Brittany.

52
00:03:54,708 --> 00:03:56,666
Your home is nearby there,
is it not?

53
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,041
[groans softly]

54
00:03:58,125 --> 00:03:59,500
If you think my grandfather

55
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:01,750
will let me borrow soldiers,
you're wrong.

56
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:03,916
We will retrieve
the sacred blade.

57
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,500
It's up to you to return home

58
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:06,791
and do what you can
to convince--

59
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:08,000
It won't work!

60
00:04:08,083 --> 00:04:10,291
You know my relationship
with that man.

61
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,583
[ALENCON]
I do.

62
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:12,791
But even so,

63
00:04:12,875 --> 00:04:15,333
you are the only one
who has a chance

64
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:18,125
at bringing us reinforcements,
Montmorency.

65
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:20,541
No, Gilles de Rais.

66
00:04:20,625 --> 00:04:22,708
♪

67
00:04:22,791 --> 00:04:24,333
[inaudible]

68
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:55,083
[thunder rumbling]

69
00:04:55,166 --> 00:04:56,083
[sighs]

70
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,541
[CATHERINE] It was raining
like this that day, too.

71
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,750
[MONTMORENCY]
Catherine.

72
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,333
It's good to see you.

73
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,666
Brother? Is that you?

74
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,250
That's right.

75
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,833
I'm sorry that I left
and came back without a word.

76
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,458
[cawing]

77
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,583
Really?

78
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:33,541
He's returned after
all this time?

79
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:36,333
-[SOLDIER] Yes, sir.
-And what does he want?

80
00:05:36,416 --> 00:05:38,000
To borrow soldiers.

81
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:39,291
Or so it seems.

82
00:05:41,666 --> 00:05:43,000
[JEAN]
Hmm.

83
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:46,041
What does that imbecile
want with my soldiers?

84
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:47,875
[thunder rumbling]

85
00:05:58,041 --> 00:05:59,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Uh...

86
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:07,833
We still have the grimoire
from the workshop.

87
00:06:07,916 --> 00:06:10,750
I'm surprised it wasn't
confiscated by the Inquisition.

88
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,250
They did try to take it away,

89
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:16,041
but we were able to bribe
a bishop to save it.

90
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:17,750
-Huh?
-[chuckles]

91
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:19,750
I didn't know
when you would return home,

92
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:21,875
so I had to make sure everything
was to your liking

93
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:23,500
for when you did.

94
00:06:23,583 --> 00:06:25,833
I had very little time
to be upset.

95
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,250
Truly.

96
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:30,041
[gasps]

97
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:32,500
Um, now that you're back, I...

98
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:34,541
[sobbing]

99
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:37,750
[BOTH gasp]

100
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,125
[MONTMORENCY]
Old man.

101
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,250
[scoffs]

102
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:43,666
[CATHERINE]
Welcome back, Grandfather.

103
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:45,375
I'll prepare your meal
right away.

104
00:06:47,375 --> 00:06:48,625
[CATHERINE gasps]

105
00:06:50,708 --> 00:06:52,333
[JEAN exhales]

106
00:06:52,416 --> 00:06:54,791
-I hear you need soldiers.
-[MONTMORENCY] Yes.

107
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:56,958
How many of them?

108
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,208
[MONTMORENCY]
Two thousand.

109
00:06:58,291 --> 00:06:59,625
[JEAN chuckles]

110
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:04,708
[exhales]

111
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,666
Very well.

112
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,708
Take as many as you like.

113
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,875
But there's one condition.

114
00:07:15,958 --> 00:07:17,166
[MONTMORENCY]
Hmm?

115
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:20,083
[JEAN]
You will marry Catherine.

116
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:21,500
[MONTMORENCY]
I thought that arrangement

117
00:07:21,583 --> 00:07:23,458
was called off years ago.

118
00:07:23,541 --> 00:07:26,666
[JEAN] Catherine's family
is incredibly wealthy.

119
00:07:26,750 --> 00:07:29,708
You would have more fortune
than the French royal family,

120
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:31,875
or the Duchy of Burgundy.

121
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:34,708
I don't remember asking you
to make me wealthy.

122
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:36,666
Besides, she's my cousin!

123
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:38,916
Well, it doesn't make
a difference to me.

124
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,250
You just won't get
any of my soldiers.

125
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,041
What kind of man
demands such a thing?!

126
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:45,083
[groans, gasps]

127
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:46,875
Montmorency!

128
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,208
-[groans]
-[gasps]

129
00:07:49,291 --> 00:07:51,583
♪

130
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,500
-[JEAN scoffs]
-[CATHERINE] Brother!

131
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,500
Are you all right? I'm here!

132
00:08:05,666 --> 00:08:07,541
[knock on door]

133
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:09,041
[door opens]

134
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:13,958
I had a feeling I might find you
in this place.

135
00:08:19,208 --> 00:08:20,500
It never occurred to me

136
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,666
that he'd still try to
force me to marry you.

137
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,958
I'm sorry.

138
00:08:24,041 --> 00:08:25,750
-You must hate this.
-[thunder rumbling]

139
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:27,125
But I don't intend to burden you

140
00:08:27,208 --> 00:08:29,250
with the crime
of marrying your cousin.

141
00:08:29,333 --> 00:08:31,166
Don't worry about the soldiers.

142
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,166
I'll think of another way.

143
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:34,875
It actually doesn't bother me.

144
00:08:34,958 --> 00:08:37,333
Because I'm quite fond of you.

145
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:41,125
Well, it goes without saying
I'm fond of you, too, of course.

146
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:43,500
But we're talking about
a different kind of--

147
00:08:43,583 --> 00:08:44,791
No we're not!

148
00:08:44,875 --> 00:08:46,541
Even if I receive God's judgment

149
00:08:46,625 --> 00:08:48,291
and I'm cast down into hell,

150
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:52,041
I still... I still want
your love more than anything!

151
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:54,125
-To do things only a wife could!
-[thunder crashes]

152
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,833
To have your child!

153
00:09:04,375 --> 00:09:08,208
[sobbing] Please, don't leave me
alone again.

154
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:34,875
[CATHERINE] It was raining
like this that day, too.

155
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:40,500
♪

156
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:55,375
[JEAN] I'm sure you've
already heard from your mother.

157
00:09:55,458 --> 00:09:57,791
You'll be marrying my grandson.

158
00:09:57,875 --> 00:09:59,625
To be quite blunt,
I am after the wealth

159
00:09:59,708 --> 00:10:01,375
that you will inherit.

160
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:03,041
Any questions?

161
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:04,375
[CATHERINE groans softly]

162
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:05,750
None at all?

163
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,208
Wise choice, girl.

164
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:09,416
[laughing]

165
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,416
♪

166
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,458
[CATHERINE]
Jean the Redbeard as he's known,

167
00:10:16,541 --> 00:10:18,375
plotted to marry
his grandson to girls

168
00:10:18,458 --> 00:10:20,416
from many different
wealthy families.

169
00:10:21,375 --> 00:10:24,583
But the fiancees who were
practically kidnapped

170
00:10:24,666 --> 00:10:27,208
and brought here,
became deeply depressed.

171
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,250
All growing frail
and passing away.

172
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:31,083
[sobbing quietly]

173
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:38,666
Huh?

174
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:48,791
[grunts]

175
00:10:51,375 --> 00:10:52,416
Huh?

176
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:57,875
[sobbing]

177
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:07,291
[JEAN]
Have you greeted her yet, boy?

178
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,625
-[MONTMORENCY] No.
-[JEAN sighs]

179
00:11:09,708 --> 00:11:11,500
I suggest you do.

180
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:17,041
Now, as you're well aware,
that girl is your cousin.

181
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:19,916
Marriage between relatives
requires the execution

182
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,083
of several
bothersome formalities.

183
00:11:22,166 --> 00:11:24,541
However, things are made
much simpler

184
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:26,166
if it's a fait accompli.

185
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,166
Huh?

186
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:31,166
[thunder rumbling]

187
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,333
[thunder crashes]

188
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:38,708
Hmm.

189
00:11:41,208 --> 00:11:42,750
[heavy breathing]

190
00:11:46,875 --> 00:11:47,958
Huh?

191
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:55,250
[groaning]

192
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:02,458
[exhales]

193
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:04,083
[MONTMORENCY]
Are you all right?

194
00:12:05,541 --> 00:12:06,541
[gasps]

195
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:10,875
[CATHERINE shuddering]

196
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:17,875
I feel... so strange.

197
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:25,083
[gasps]

198
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:26,750
♪

199
00:12:32,958 --> 00:12:36,125
From this moment on, I'm going
to be your big brother.

200
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:38,166
I promise to always protect you.

201
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:40,833
[sighs]

202
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:47,541
[gasps]
Where are we? I'm gonna fall!

203
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:49,333
[MONTMORENCY] I know this forest
inside and out.

204
00:12:49,416 --> 00:12:53,000
Besides, you don't think
I'd let you get hurt, do you?

205
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:54,291
[laughing]

206
00:12:55,416 --> 00:12:58,208
[CATHERINE] The marriage
proceedings didn't go smoothly,

207
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:00,041
and I ended up
living in the castle

208
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:01,791
as his little sister instead.

209
00:13:03,375 --> 00:13:05,375
The grandson
of Jean the Redbeard,

210
00:13:05,458 --> 00:13:07,458
Gilles de Rais
Montmorency-Laval.

211
00:13:08,458 --> 00:13:11,583
[MONTMORENCY weakly]
I'll protect Catherine.

212
00:13:11,666 --> 00:13:13,208
[grunting]

213
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:16,583
[CATHERINE]
On that fateful, rainy night,

214
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,500
he became my brother.

215
00:13:18,583 --> 00:13:21,208
Montmorency! Montmorency!

216
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:23,416
Will you pat my head,
Montmorency?

217
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,458
Ooh, me too, pretty please?

218
00:13:25,541 --> 00:13:27,041
[MONTMORENCY]
I don't see why not.

219
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:28,416
One at a time, okay?

220
00:13:30,583 --> 00:13:32,750
This lady is really pretty.

221
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:35,125
Pretty lady, can I touch you?

222
00:13:35,208 --> 00:13:37,083
-[laughter]
-[CATHERINE] Uh...

223
00:13:40,208 --> 00:13:42,333
Come on. Be gentle, you guys.

224
00:13:42,416 --> 00:13:45,041
Catherine's my little sister,
so be careful not to hurt her.

225
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:47,458
♪

226
00:13:49,041 --> 00:13:51,708
-[chuckling]
-[laughs]

227
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,375
That's the first time
I've seen you laugh.

228
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:58,791
I guess you're right, brother.

229
00:13:58,875 --> 00:14:00,875
[ALL laughing]

230
00:14:12,916 --> 00:14:14,000
[SOLDIER]
Farewell.

231
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:15,125
[RICHEMONT]
Thanks for the report.

232
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,583
[RICHEMONT]
So, Montmorency is in Champtoce.

233
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:24,416
I want to see him,
but what good would come of it?

234
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,416
[SOLDIERS yelling]

235
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:35,833
[yawning]

236
00:14:35,916 --> 00:14:38,416
[SOLDIER] Lord Glasdale,
please prepare for battle!

237
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,833
[sighs]
All right.

238
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:41,291
[gunshot]

239
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,208
Which one of you
wants to die next?

240
00:14:44,291 --> 00:14:46,458
[yelling]

241
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:48,125
[shouting]

242
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:51,250
[grunts]

243
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:55,625
The merciful La Hire only holds
back on women and children!

244
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:58,041
There'll be no pity for you men.

245
00:14:58,125 --> 00:15:00,458
Ah! You truly are
the most beautiful

246
00:15:00,541 --> 00:15:02,166
when you're on a rampage.

247
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:03,791
Much better than when
you're brooding over

248
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,166
your responsibility as a leader,
that doesn't suit you--

249
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,250
[screams]

250
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:09,250
Shut your mouth and fight.

251
00:15:09,333 --> 00:15:10,666
I don't want you
screwing this up

252
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:13,083
when we've already been paid
for it in advance.

253
00:15:14,083 --> 00:15:16,625
♪

254
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:20,083
The Mythical Joyeuse is
a small price to pay for Jeanne.

255
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:23,458
-I'm counting on you, La Hire.
-[gunshot]

256
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:27,125
[LA HIRE]
Forgive me, Jeanne.

257
00:15:27,208 --> 00:15:29,291
It was a mistake
to leave you behind.

258
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:33,458
Hear me, English scum.

259
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:36,625
I'll make every one of you pay
for hurting a child.

260
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:38,041
[GLASDALE]
It's just a reinforcement

261
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,791
of a hundred mercenaries.

262
00:15:39,875 --> 00:15:42,791
You must not be taking this
seriously if you need my help.

263
00:15:42,875 --> 00:15:44,125
[SOLDIER]
I apologize, sir.

264
00:15:44,208 --> 00:15:45,791
Hmm.

265
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:47,208
[GLASDALE]
Noire.

266
00:15:47,291 --> 00:15:49,791
Prove that I'm right
to not worry about you.

267
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:52,791
Put that Holy Grail
to use and heal.

268
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:06,000
-[door opens]
-[footsteps approaching]

269
00:16:06,083 --> 00:16:08,000
[JEAN]
You haven't departed yet?

270
00:16:08,083 --> 00:16:10,583
Then share a bed
with Catherine tonight.

271
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,500
Do so and you will have
your soldiers

272
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:14,541
as well as new inheritance.

273
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:17,500
Do you wish to decline
all the fortune and power

274
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:21,291
accumulated by Jean
the Redbeard's tireless schemes

275
00:16:21,375 --> 00:16:23,416
or do you wish to inherit it?

276
00:16:23,500 --> 00:16:26,166
[MONTMORENCY] Tell me,
why must you try so hard

277
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:27,916
to pass down
your wealth to me?

278
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,000
[JEAN laughs]

279
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:30,875
It is the tradition of all men

280
00:16:30,958 --> 00:16:32,041
who are born in Reims--

281
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:34,208
Hmm.

282
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,291
♪

283
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:45,333
I think you were truly ready
to kill me just now.

284
00:16:45,416 --> 00:16:47,500
[MONTMORENCY]
That's right.

285
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:50,583
I've become a different man
since leaving these walls.

286
00:16:57,916 --> 00:16:59,500
-[rumbling]
-Hmm?

287
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:03,541
♪

288
00:17:08,083 --> 00:17:09,250
Hmm?

289
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:12,958
It's been a long time,
Nicolas Flamel.

290
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:19,000
Are you here to laugh
at my foolishness?

291
00:17:19,083 --> 00:17:21,583
You were right, as it turns out.

292
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:24,125
I should have killed Gilles
all those years ago.

293
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:27,250
♪

294
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:29,041
[NICOLAS]
If you do not kill him now,

295
00:17:29,125 --> 00:17:31,958
calamity will fall
upon the world.

296
00:17:32,041 --> 00:17:33,500
That's absurd.

297
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:36,250
I don't believe in astrology
or numerology,

298
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:38,041
or whatever it is
that you practice.

299
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:39,708
Save your breath.

300
00:17:39,791 --> 00:17:42,125
[NICOLAS] This boy,
Gilles de Montmorency-Laval

301
00:17:42,208 --> 00:17:43,875
has the imprint of the beast,

302
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:46,666
as predicted by
the apocalyptic literature.

303
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:49,791
But he can still be saved, yet.

304
00:17:49,875 --> 00:17:52,875
Even the most privileged men
are still human.

305
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:55,333
They have a limit
to what they can attain.

306
00:17:55,416 --> 00:17:57,041
As long as he remains human,

307
00:17:57,125 --> 00:18:00,500
the latent qualities of the
demon lord will stay dormant.

308
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:03,541
He will live a normal life
with human limitations.

309
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:06,583
Hmm. I remember your warning.

310
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:08,708
I'll make sure he stays human.

311
00:18:10,583 --> 00:18:12,458
But Gilles has already
been attracted

312
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:14,333
by the realm of alchemy.

313
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:17,166
He's been seduced by something
beyond the limitations

314
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:19,458
of a normal man.

315
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:22,541
Even that look he gave me
was inhuman.

316
00:18:22,625 --> 00:18:24,458
I've committed countless
evil deeds,

317
00:18:24,541 --> 00:18:27,166
but that chilled me
to the bone.

318
00:18:30,791 --> 00:18:32,166
[NICOLAS]
Where are you going?

319
00:18:34,166 --> 00:18:36,041
[thunder rumbling]

320
00:18:45,875 --> 00:18:47,125
[knock on door]

321
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,250
[door opens]

322
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:50,041
Brother.

323
00:18:50,125 --> 00:18:51,500
[MONTMORENCY]
Forgive me, Catherine.

324
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:52,666
[CATHERINE]
Huh?

325
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,500
[MONTMORENCY]
I cannot marry you.

326
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:58,333
Not because we're cousins.

327
00:18:58,416 --> 00:19:01,041
Because I swore an oath
to the maiden of Domremy.

328
00:19:01,125 --> 00:19:03,791
I have made
a promise to Jeanne.

329
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:05,416
♪

330
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:07,000
[inaudible]

331
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:13,000
That girl is all alone.

332
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:15,541
There's nowhere in this world
that she belongs now.

333
00:19:17,958 --> 00:19:19,625
I'm responsible for that.

334
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,666
For making her
what she's become.

335
00:19:22,750 --> 00:19:25,833
What about the soldiers
waiting for reinforcements?

336
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:28,458
What will Princess Charlotte do
without help?

337
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:33,875
What about the girl
in front of you,

338
00:19:33,958 --> 00:19:36,000
who's just as alone
as that maiden?

339
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:40,500
♪

340
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:58,625
I'll take those soldiers,
as you promised.

341
00:19:58,708 --> 00:20:01,250
♪

342
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:07,541
[CATHERINE] You must love
the maiden of Domremy.

343
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Love her?

344
00:20:11,500 --> 00:20:13,083
That's right.

345
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:14,541
[MONTMORENCY]
Me?

346
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:16,791
Even if the whole world
had turned against you,

347
00:20:16,875 --> 00:20:20,083
you would still dedicate
yourself to her entirely.

348
00:20:20,166 --> 00:20:22,041
That's the definition of love.

349
00:20:22,125 --> 00:20:23,416
Don't you see?

350
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:26,541
♪

351
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:31,875
[gasps]

352
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:33,333
[MONTMORENCY]
I love Jeanne?

353
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:35,625
I have an idea.

354
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:37,625
Let's say that we laid
together tonight.

355
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:40,083
Then you can take the troops
you need tomorrow.

356
00:20:41,291 --> 00:20:43,166
[MONTMORENCY]
And you're all right with that?

357
00:20:45,291 --> 00:20:47,250
[CATHERINE]
I just have one request.

358
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:48,291
What is it?

359
00:20:49,583 --> 00:20:53,208
Hold me in your arms
until the sun rises.

360
00:20:53,291 --> 00:20:54,625
Just like back then.

361
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:02,000
[MONTMORENCY] I was stuck
in the alchemy workshop

362
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:03,833
for seven years.

363
00:21:03,916 --> 00:21:05,291
And only now do I discover

364
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:08,458
that you've become
more mature than I, Catherine.

365
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:10,708
[crying]

366
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:19,375
[NICOLAS] Oftentimes,
it's impossible for one

367
00:21:19,458 --> 00:21:21,833
to change the fate
that life has given them.

368
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,625
However, perhaps it is
different for someone

369
00:21:25,708 --> 00:21:27,458
who has experienced love.

370
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:31,583
At least, that's what I want
to believe is the case.

371
00:21:35,458 --> 00:21:36,958
[MONTMORENCY]
I've been true to my word.

372
00:21:38,708 --> 00:21:41,458
You'd better do
the same, Alencon.

373
00:21:43,166 --> 00:21:45,791
Mercenaries and knights alike,

374
00:21:45,875 --> 00:21:47,833
hear me now!

375
00:21:47,916 --> 00:21:49,708
We ride to Orleans,

376
00:21:49,791 --> 00:21:52,291
where we shall turn
the tide of battle!

377
00:21:52,375 --> 00:21:53,916
[cheering]

378
00:23:27,666 --> 00:23:29,208
[NARRATOR] Would you be
interested in the story

379
00:23:29,291 --> 00:23:30,958
of an earnest high school
baseball team manager?

380
00:23:31,041 --> 00:23:32,166
I didn't think so.

381
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:33,625
What you're interested in
is breasts.

382
00:23:33,708 --> 00:23:35,708
Now, imagine if Batard
had large mammaries.

383
00:23:35,791 --> 00:23:37,666
Would that not make you question
your own existence?

384
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:39,833
Episode 8,
"Return of the Female Saint."

385
00:23:39,916 --> 00:23:41,916
Say, Alencon,
care to weigh in on this?

386
00:23:43,916 --> 00:23:45,583
[WOMAN]
Je veux un enfant de toi.

